node.text: Such a rad time with an awesome group of peoples. The @GridExperience definitely sets the bar (and sets it pretty high) for me when it comes to indoor karting. Combine that with a this crew of friends and fam: Jeremy McGrath, Sage Kotsenburg, Zak Hale, Davey Coombs (founder of Racer X), Zac Mertens (of Hoonigan Racing), etc. - plus Jett and Hunter Lawrence were two of the top three fastest of the night (same positions as they finished in the 250 Main of the Supercross race this past weekend!). Jeremy’s daughter (Rhowan) and my daughter (Lia) both had two of the top lap five times also (yep, we’re proud Dads!). Good times!

node.title: Rad time karting at The Grid Experience with friends and fam.

node.text: The @GridExperience’s indoor kart track is really amazing. It’s a half mile long, 3-level, has two banked corners, a drop - and the electric karts have a boost button! node.text: This weekend will be my first competitive drive in a Subaru since 2009. With only one proper day of testing before @AlexGelsomino and I show up this weekend to the @OlympusRally (3rd round of the @ARA_Rally Championship) it will be interesting to see how quickly I can get fully comfortable in it and run at full tilt. But so far, the car looks (livery by @ItsALiving) and feels (built and prepped by Vermont SportsCar) great! Check out this week's episode on my YouTube channel (link in bio) for the livery reveal, and to hear about all our plans for a wild year! #gravelslayingaction

node.text: Here’s another AINT CARE moment from the vault: @AlexGelsomino and I lost our front right side wheel midway through Stage 3 (of Oregon Trail Rally in 2013) due to a freak mechanical failure. We kept the hammer down and finished that stage, and then continued on to run another full stage on just 3 wheels, rather than settling for a DNF. We finished the race 2nd overall - all because we were able to drive through this #AINTCARE situation!

node.text: AIN’T CARE, rally cross example: after qualifying first, winning each of the heats, and leading the first 5 laps of the Final in the 2012 GRC race in Las Vegas, the ECU/control panel in my race car caught fire. I continued the race for as long as I could, but the fumes from the fire were starting to burn my lungs. I led and raced for as long as I could but eventually had to stop. I truly tried to AIN’T CARE as long as I could, but wasn’t willing to die for the win. 🤷‍♂️ #AINTCARE #pressonregardless

node.text: Lots of rain prior to The Rally in the 100 Acre Wood this year made for some very wet and rough stretches of the race stages. This video from Stage 12 is a sample of that at this year’s race in Salem, Missouri. @AlexGelsomino and I were fastest on this stage during the race, helping us secure 2nd place overall. Click the link to see the full on-board video from the entire 10.84 mile stage. #100AW

node.text: Battling for a podium is never easy, especially with opponents like Travis Pastrana. And when we are all battling rain, sketchy mud, sandy ruts, etc, that doesn’t help either! Check out @alexgelsomino and I going flat out through the Minnesota forests in the new episode on my YouTube channel (link in bio). #OjibweForestsRally

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Ken Block on September 02, 2021 tagging @alexgelsomino, @monsterenergy, @dcosseboom, @rotiform, and @dirtycarwindow. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: Just because it’s raining and wet doesn’t mean we’re not going to huck it off every jump! It was great coming back to the Ojibwe Forests Rally - the last time we raced it was 8 years ago (and was a win). And while we didn’t get the win this year, the points for 2nd overall are good for our championship standings. See these jumps in full speed in my latest video (link in bio). #OjibweForestsRally

node.text: My wife and her co-driver Michelle Miller completed the Ojibwe Forests Rally last weekend ahead of more than half the field! It was a tough event for her small FWD race car (because of rain, sand ruts, mud, etc.) but she placed 7th out of 15 competitors in the O2WD class, and 26th overall. Considering this is only her second race in two years she’s been doing great and really getting comfortable behind the wheel again. #fastwife #FiestaR2 #OjibweForestsRally

node.text: Just finished listening to my good friend, skate photography legend, Mike Blabac (@blabacphoto) on The Nine Club podcast. Give it a listen to hear some great behind-the-scenes stories from moments like shooting with pro skateboarder @joshkalis to some of the Gymkhana films. Mike is responsible for some of my most iconic photos: sliding under a 747 in Dubai for Gymkhana EIGHT, the world record jump I did for the TV show Stunt Junkies, the Randy’s Donuts shot from Gymkhana SEVEN, and the Russian Hill Jump from Gymkhana FIVE - and many more. Enjoy! #TheNineClub #Gymkhana

node.text: The Hoonigans built the Warthog from Halo! Every panel inside and out on this thing was built in Area 69 (Hoonigan’s shop space for secret builds) by @suppymk4 and @grimmaro along with a few other helping hands. It was really hard keeping this build a secret but so worth it seeing everyone’s reaction to it on the red carpet at the Free Guy movie premiere with Ryan Reynolds. And, this thing really works: it features a 1000hp+ twin-turbo Ford V8 (same as the Hoonicorn V2), all the off-road suspension we could throw at it, 43” tires, and 4-wheel steering, etc. It’s a beautiful build and ready to shred!

node.text: Great stages, rain, rutted sand corners, jumps, fun Super Special stage for the fans - the Ojibwe Forests Rally had it all! @alexgelsomino and I tried our best, but we ended up on the 2nd step of the podium. Obviously, we are always gunning for first place (which we did last time we were here), but it was good to run this rally again - and our 8 year absence at this race meant we had to write a lot of new pace notes. I look forward to a better battle next year! #OjibweForestsRally
